s also a gang of survivalists who have connections to this cozy little group, and end up being close to the action; much too close, in fact. It's enough to make you dizzy <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/uprojectorion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>projectorion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(1/19/02 3:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.fas.org/nuke/hew/Usa/Tests/Rwmohawk2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Footfall</span><hr size=1> I hate that aswell. All too common in movies today and makes you want to walk out. It does spoil a novel when I come across it. This might be a small world but when the coincidences pile up to absurd heights the realism vanishes. <br>
